  "source_notes": "B.R. in hand from Steinbrecher on which the year is clearly typed as 1929; however, Jim Gorham in 2004 writes to PT:  I have 2 good sources which suggest the Dossier year of birth may be in error: 1)  A University of California memorium for Donald Ray Cressey (1919 to 1987), Professer Emeritus, a sociologist who is credited with writing some of the books mentioned in the bio. PT speculates that the clerk in the birth records office mistyped year of birth as it is unusual for people to say they are born 10 years BEFORE their official birth time. 2) The California Death Index. Place of birth matches (Minnesota); month and day of birth match (April 27), but the year is again 1919.\\n\\nIn October 2017: year of birth changed to 1919, assuming 1929 was a mistype as the online biographies all seem to have 1919 as birth year. His Wikipedia bio also states that he got his Ph.D. from Indiana University in 1950. If born in 1929, he would have been 21. If in 1919, 31.\\n",
